HEADWORD: Greedy
<hw>Greed"y</hw> <pr>(gr⟦emac⟧d"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Greedier</adjf>
<pr>(-⟦icr⟧*⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Greediest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>gredi</ets>, AS.
<ets>gr⟦aemac⟧dig</ets>, <ets>gr⟦emac⟧dig</ets>; akin to D.
<ets>gretig</ets>, OS. <ets>gr⟦amac⟧dag</ets>, OHG.
<ets>gr⟦amac⟧tag</ets>, Dan. <ets>graadig</ets>, OSw. <ets>gradig</ets>,
<ets>gr⟦aring⟧dig</ets>, Icel. <ets>gr⟦amac⟧⟦edh⟧ugr</ets>, Goth.
<ets>gr⟦emac⟧dags</ets> greedy, <ets>gr⟦emac⟧d⟦emac⟧n</ets> to be
hungry; cf. Skr. <ets>g⟦rsdot⟧dh</ets> to be greedy. Cf.
<er>Greed.</er>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having a keen appetite for food
or drink; ravenous; voracious; very hungry; -- followed by of; <as>as, a
lion that is <ex>greedy</ex> of his prey</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having a keen desire for anything; vehemently
desirous; eager to obtain; avaricious; <as>as, <er>greedy</er> of
gain</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Greedy-gut</ent>⟦br⟧
